────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────    
 Context

 The Python file week91_intermediate_git_stored_procedure/add_1.py contains:

   from snowflake.snowpark.functions import col

   def add_one_to_column(session, table_name, column_name):
       df = session.table(table_name)
       updated_df = df.withColumn(column_name, col(column_name) + 1)
       return updated_df

 The repo https://github.com/Sakatoku/Frosty-Friday/ is public, so no credentials/secret are needed.

 Implementation Steps

 Step 1: Create an API Integration (no auth, public repo)

   CREATE OR REPLACE API INTEGRATION frosty_friday_git_integration
     API_PROVIDER = git_https_api
     API_ALLOWED_PREFIXES = ('https://github.com/Sakatoku')
     ENABLED = TRUE;

 Step 2: Create the Git Repository clone

   CREATE OR REPLACE GIT REPOSITORY frosty_friday_repo
     API_INTEGRATION = frosty_friday_git_integration
     ORIGIN = 'https://github.com/Sakatoku/Frosty-Friday.git';

 Step 3: Fetch latest from remote

   ALTER GIT REPOSITORY frosty_friday_repo FETCH;

 Step 4: Create the Stored Procedure referencing the .py file

   CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE add_one_to_column(table_name VARCHAR, column_name VARCHAR)
     RETURNS TABLE()
     LANGUAGE PYTHON
     RUNTIME_VERSION = '3.12'
     PACKAGES = ('snowflake-snowpark-python')
     IMPORTS = ('@frosty_friday_repo/branches/main/week91_intermediate_git_stored_procedure/add_1.py')
     HANDLER = 'add_1.add_one_to_column';

 The HANDLER is add_1.add_one_to_column — module name (add_1 from the filename) + function name.

 Step 5: Verify by calling the procedure

   CALL add_one_to_column('<some_table>', '<some_column>');

 Verification

 • Confirm the API integration is created (SHOW API INTEGRATIONS)
 • Confirm the Git repo is created and fetched (SHOW GIT REPOSITORIES, list files with LS @frosty_friday_repo/branches/main/week91_intermediate_git_stored_procedure/)
 • Confirm the procedure is created (SHOW PROCEDURES LIKE 'ADD_ONE_TO_COLUMN')
 • Call the procedure on a test table to verify it works

 Critical Files / Objects

 • week91_intermediate_git_stored_procedure/add_1.py — The Python handler file in the Git repo
 • API integration frosty_friday_git_integration — Allows Snowflake to access GitHub
 • Git repository frosty_friday_repo — Snowflake clone of the GitHub repo
 • Stored procedure add_one_to_column — The procedure to create

 Note: Creating the API integration requires ACCOUNTADMIN or a role with CREATE INTEGRATION privilege. If that's not available, I'll need you to grant it or run that step yourself.

